                    <ab>(C.) In nomine domini nostri Iesu Christi regis aeterni. <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/173">Otto</persName> divina favente <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus. Quia imperialis
                        magnificentia pia et larga erga dei cultores et ecclesiarum dei recuperatrix
                        et restauratrix esse debet, ut id agendo premium mereatur consequi
                        sempiternum: idcirco omnium fidelium sanctae dei ecclesiae nostrorumque
                        presentium ac futurorum devotio noverit, qualiter nos consultu ac interventu
                        venerabilis <rs key="#Bishops">episcopi</rs>
                        <persName key="#Bishops #fidelisOf"><name ref="Hubertus"
                            >Huberti</name></persName> karissimi <rs key="#fidelisOf">fidelis</rs>
                        nostri adquiescentes aliquantam <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terram</rs>
                        quam bone memorie <persName key="#Bishops"><name ref="Petrus"
                            >Petrus</name></persName> episcopus ad utilitatem <rs key="#Canons"
                            >canonicorum</rs> in <rs key="#Churches">ecclesia</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/1402"
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Villas #Curtes #Landed_possessions #Forests #Gualdi #Size #Wine #Agricultural_workers #Pagus #Census #Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium #Churches #Archpriests #Priests #Archdeacons #Deacons #Other_clerics #Canons"
                            >sancti Donati confessoris et martiris Christi</orgName> ibi pro tempore
                        deo servientium distribuit et antecessores nostri <rs key="#Emperor/king"
                            >i[mperat]ores et reges</rs> postea confirmaverunt et suo proprio <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Inflow #Gift">dono</rs> concesserunt, videlicet
                            <rs key="#Wine">vineam</rs> unam ad <placeName
                            key="#Cereals #Wine #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Pinum</placeName> cum <rs key="#Cereals">campo</rs> ibi prope similiter
                        ad Pinum nominante et <rs key="#Landed_possessions">campum alterum qui
                            dicitur pratum Sale</rs> nec non <rs key="#Curtes">corticellam</rs> unam
                        que dicitur ad <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/1431"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Clane</placeName></geogName> cum sua pertinentia et aliam
                        corticellam que vocatur <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/1432"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Moionam</placeName></geogName> sub integritate, sicut discernitur
                        in scripto a iam nominato Petro episcopo facto, <rs key="#Churches"
                            >ecclesiam</rs> quoque sancti <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1427">Petri in castello</orgName> quam dive
                        memorie <persName ref="#people/72">Lotharius</persName> pro remedio anime
                        sue canonicos ibi servientes habere concessit, nec non et <rs key="#Villas"
                            >villas</rs> tres quarum una nominatur <geogName
                            key="#Villas #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/1433"><placeName
                                key="#Villas #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Durna</placeName></geogName>, altera <geogName
                            key="#Villas #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/1434"><placeName
                                key="#Villas #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Plica</placeName></geogName>, tertia <geogName
                            key="#Villas #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/1435"><placeName
                                key="#Villas #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Spegia</placeName></geogName>, quas predictus Lotharius canonicis
                        confirmavit, <rs key="#Periodic_markets">mercatum</rs> insuper unum quod
                        celebratur in missa sancti Ilariani, <rs key="#Curtes">cortem</rs> etiam que
                        nominatur <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/1436"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Camenina</placeName></geogName> et est in <placeName
                            ref="#places/1803">castro Felicitatis</placeName> cum <rs
                            key="#Churches">ecclesia</rs> in honore <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            >sancti Andreae</orgName> edificata cum omni [sua pertine]ntia quam
                        prefatus imperator canonicis concessit, <rs key="#Landed_possessions">campum
                            insuper unum qui vocatur Pisinule</rs> et consistit in <rs key="#Pagus"
                            >pago</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Pagus" ref="#places/505">Aritiense</placeName> cum omnibus
                        suis appenditiis, ut pretaxatus imperator eis concessit, <rs key="#Curtes"
                            >cortem</rs> namque qui vocatur <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/1437"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Colonaria</placeName></geogName> cum omni sua pertinentia, per hoc
                        nostrum imperiale preceptum canonicis qui nunc ibi serviunt, scilicet
                            <persName key="#Archdeacons #Canons"><name ref="Grasulfus"
                                >Grasulfo</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Archdeacons">archidiacono</rs>, <persName
                            key="#Archpriests #Canons"><name ref="Suavericus"
                            >Suauerico</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Archpriests">archipresbytero</rs> et primicerio, <persName
                            key="#Canons"><name ref="Sapiens">Sapienti</name></persName> gramatico,
                            <persName key="#Priests #Canons"><name ref="Arulfus"
                            >Erolfo</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbytero</rs>, <persName key="#Canons"><name
                                ref="Stratarius">Stratario</name></persName> maiori scole, <persName
                            key="#Other_clerics #Canons"><name ref="Iohannes"
                            >Iohannes</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Other_clerics">clericus</rs> et custos, <persName
                            key="#Priests #Canons"><name ref="Iohannes">Iohannes</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbytero</rs>, <persName key="#Priests #Canons"><name
                                ref="Aldebertus">Altiperto</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbytero</rs>, <persName key="#Deacons #Canons"><name
                                ref="Michael">Michael</name></persName> et [<persName
                            key="#Deacons #Canons"><name ref="Iohannes">Iohannes</name></persName>]
                        et <persName key="#Deacons #Canons"><name ref="Aimo">Agimo</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Deacons">diaconibus</rs> et reliquis qui ibi in presenti serviunt
                        eorumque successoribus qui futuris temporibus ibi servierint, restituimus
                        confirmamus pleniterque corrobor[a]mus. De iure insuper regni nostri donamus
                        predicti loci canonicis <rs key="#Curtes">[corti]cellam</rs> unam qui
                        coniacet in avocabulo <placeName
                            key="#Curtes #Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Toppo</placeName> una cum ipsa <rs key="#Forests">silva qui dicitur
                                <geogName
                                key="#Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#estates/2350"><placeName
                                    key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                    >Arbororum</placeName></geogName></rs> et una cum omni
                        pertinentia et adiacentia sua et cum ipsa <rs key="#Gualdi">gualdemania</rs>
                        qui coniacet in <placeName key="#Gualdi">Uico</placeName> et in <placeName
                            key="#Gualdi">Policiano</placeName> et in <placeName key="#Gualdi"
                            >Peciano</placeName> et per illorum vocabulas, et <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">campum unum qui dicitur Longoria</rs>
                        coniacente prope <placeName>Perilasium</placeName> qui capere videtur <rs
                            key="#Size">modia viginti</rs>, ita videlicet ut nec rector eiusdem
                        sedis nec cuiuslibet potestatis persona de prefatis rebus vel de eorum
                        pertinentiis seu de his que divina pietas inibi ageri voluerit illis aliquam
                        inferre presumat contrarietatem vel deminorationem ullam ingerere adtemptet.
                        Confirmamus eis scilicet <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terram</rs> quam
                            <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/79">Hugo</persName> rex <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Inflow #Gift #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >de sua proprietate eisdem canonicis concessit</rs>, id est <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">campum de Piunta</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">campum de Graticiata</rs>, ut illis absque
                        aliqua minoratione aut cuiuslibet potestatis contrarietate perhennis
                        perseveret temporibus. Statuimus quoque ut sit ipsa canonica cum canonicis
                        ipsius loci sub magisterio et regimine Grasulfi archidiaconi et Suauerici
                        archipresbyteri eorumque successorum, facientes pari voto communique
                        consensu de frugibus et reditibus quod in ipsa canonica annualiter dominus
                        dederit seu de elemosinis absolute et libere, ut canonici facere debent,
                        absque ullius contradictione vel molestatione. Quia <rs>Tuscis</rs>
                        consuetudo est ut, accepto ab ecclesia <rs
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis">libello</rs>, in contumatiam
                        convertantur contra ecclesiam, ita ut vix aut numquam constitutum reddant
                            <rs key="#Census">censum</rs>, precipimus modisque omnibus iubemus, ut
                        non episcopus vel canonicus libellum aut aliquod scriptum alicui homini
                        faciant, nisi <rs key="#Agricultural_workers">laboratoribus</rs> qui fructum
                        terre ecclesiae et ca[nonicis ipsius loc]i reddant sine molestia vel
                        contradiction[e aliq]ua. Precipimus quoque ut in ipsa canonica nulla
                        [deinceps ad]iciatur persona absque communi consensu, ne propter hoc aliqua
                        inter illos oriatur discordia. Pro maiori quoque illorum securitate
                        recipimus illos cum omnibus illorum mobilibus et inmobilibus rebus illis
                        iuste et legaliter pertinentibus sub nostre <rs
                            key="#Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium">tuitionis munburdo</rs>, quatenus
                        secure vivere deoque servire et pro nobis statuque regni nostri remedioque
                        anime nostre orare illis iugiter delectet. Si quis igitur huius nostre
                        confirmationis precepti et munburdi violator aut contradictor extiterit,
                        sciat se compositurum <rs key="#Penalty">auri optimi libras centum</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Camera_regis">medietatem kamere nostre</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities">medietatem prefatis canonicis
                            qui in ecclesia beati Donati pro tempore servierint</rs>. Quod ut verius
                        credatur dilige[nti]usque ab omnibus observetur, manu propria roborantes de
                        anulo nostro subter anotari iussimus. Signum domni Ottonis magni imperatoris
                        (M.) augusti. <persName key="#Chancellor"><name ref="Liutgerus"
                                >Liutgerius</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> advicem <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Bishops"><name ref="Wido"
                            >Uuidonis</name></persName> episcopi et <rs key="#Archchancellor"
                            >archicancellarii</rs> recognovi et subscripsi. (SI. D.) Data VI. idus
                        mai. anno dominicae incarnationis DCCCCLXIII, indictione VI, anno imperii
                        magni Ottonis imperatoris augusti II; actum <placeName ref="#places/1861"
                            >monte Feretrano ad sanctum Leonem</placeName>.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
